The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                               Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Cement manufacturer ACC has divested its entire stake in its subsidiary ACC Machinery Company to diesel engine manufacturer HNG Group for Rs 45 crore, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. ACC Machinerys net profit for the year ended December 31 was Rs 9.75 crore and total income was Rs 63.24 crore. ACC Machinery had also paid a dividend of Rs 190 per share.                             
	 Hyundai Motor India has received 60,000 export orders for its small car, the i10, which was launched in October 2007. The company started accepting export orders for the car from December 2007.                             
	 Garden Reach Shipbuilders amp; Engineers has handed over GRSE Yard 3015 (Kesari) to the Navy on February 21. Kesari is an amphibious assault ship that can carry aircraft, battle tanks, army vehicles and troops.                             
	 Sita Shree Food products has launched a public issue of Rs 31.50 crore. The price band of the offer has been fixed at Rs 27 to Rs 30. The shares will be listed on the BSE and the NSE. The company will invest the net proceeds of the issue to finance its expansion plan. The offer will close on March 14, 2008.                            
	 Chabria Infotech has entered into a partnership with Adobe to launch the latters latest animation software for the Indian animation industry. The software solutions will include Adobes Digital School Collection and Future Pro Solutions for web development.                             
	 NCR Corporation has implemented a cheque truncation system for the Reserve Bank of India. The system includes cheque mark image processing solution, image mark electronic cheque presentment with image exchange software and image mark NCompass archive.                             
	 Reliance Communications has slashed prices of its Internet data cards. The companys Netconnect PCMCIA data card and Netconnect USB Modem data card will now be available at Rs 2,990 and Rs 2,850, respectively.                                                                                                                    ADVERTISEMENT                   
